        "title": "Add development trace UI",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a source-checkout-only development LLM trace recorder for full prompt/tool payload debugging.\n- Exposes `traces.capabilities`, `traces.list`, and `traces.get` Gateway methods behind explicit development flags, admin scope, and a strict direct-loopback browser Control UI grant.\n- Adds a Traces Control UI view with a compact trace selector plus readable prompt-message, tool-argument, parameter, response, and raw-payload sections, with mocked Gateway E2E coverage.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/llm-dev-tracing.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run ui/src/styles/components.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check ui/src/ui/views/traces.ts ui/src/styles/components.css ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --prompt 'Only review the tracing UI patch in ui/src/ui/views/traces.ts, ui/src/styles/components.css, and ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts. Treat unrelated untracked docs/refactor/*.md files as out of scope; they pre-existed this task and should not be reported.'`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Development-only tracing UI shows captured LLM prompt payloads and tool schemas while remaining disabled outside an explicit source-checkout loopback debugging session.\n\nReal environment tested: Local Control UI Playwright/Chromium E2E server with mocked Gateway WebSocket responses, using the repo's Control UI E2E helper.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Captured a Playwright browser recording through the Traces route with mock trace capability enabled, including hidden reasoning/tool-call response deltas and visible answer deltas, then ran the committed trace E2E command above.\n\nEvidence after fix: Current recording captured at local artifact `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/tracing-ui-readable/page@c8ae1e5a24ef13f63ff45930fd196950.webm`; screenshot captured at `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/tracing-ui-readable/tracing-ui-readable.png`; E2E asserts the compact trace row omits request-size metadata, prompt text is readable, tool arguments render as rows, visible response text renders, and hidden reasoning/tool-call deltas do not appear as answer text.\n\nObserved result after fix: The Traces tab rendered the selected `openai/gpt-5.5` trace with a narrow left selector and a readable detail panel for system/user messages, tool parameters, invocation parameters, and final answer text, while still keeping raw message/schema/payload disclosures available.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live provider request with real credentials; the proof intentionally uses deterministic mocked Gateway data to avoid recording real prompts or secrets.\n",
